  <p><strong>Thank you for sharing the blurb below.</strong></p>
  <p>The Illinois Network of Charter Schools (INCS) will host its <a href="https://www.incschools.org/events/tjf/">13th annual Teacher Job Fair</a> on Saturday, April 7th, 2018 at Perspectives/IIT Math & Science Academy (3663 South Wabash Avenue, Chicago, IL 60653). Representatives from the state’s charter schools will be on hand to recruit hundreds of teachers, social workers, counselors, nurses, and other administrators - such as marketing managers, college coaches, and finance operators.  You can learn more about the FREE fair and upload your resume to the year-round resume bank <a href="www.teacherjobfair.org">here.</a> </p>
  <p>Some of the great features of the job fair include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Free networking opportunity + access to over 100 school leaders looking to hire talented candidates</li>
    <li>Opportunity to interview on-site following the meet-and-greet portion of the fair, by invite only</li>
    <li>A year-round <a href="www.teacherjobfair.org">online resume bank</a> where candidates can submit their info to the 145+ campuses and set up interviews remotely</li>
    <li>Per charter law, students and alumni of all academic backgrounds are welcome to apply  </li>
  </ul>
  <p>For more information, contact INCS Manager of Talent & Special Projects, Stephanie Arias, at sarias@incschools.org
